#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.23:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Anuttariyavagga"
msgstr "3. Unsurpassable"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Bhayasutta"
msgstr "23. Dangers"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.311"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.23:1.1"
msgid "“‘Bhayan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "“‘Danger’, mendicants, is a term for sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "an6.23:1.2"
msgid "‘dukkhan’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘Suffering’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:1.3"
msgid "‘rogo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘disease’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:1.4"
msgid "‘gaṇḍo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘boil’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:1.5"
msgid "‘saṅgo’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ;"
msgstr "‘tie’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:1.6"
msgid "‘paṅko’ti, bhikkhave, kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "and ‘bog’ are terms for sensual pleasures."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.23:2.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, ‘bhayan’ti kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ?"
msgstr "And why is ‘danger’ a term for sensual pleasures?"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.2"
msgid ""
"Kāmarāgarattāyaṃ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi bhayā na "
"parimuccati, samparāyikāpi bhayā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘bhayan’ti "
"kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Someone who is caught up in sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is "
"not freed from dangers in the present life or in lives to come. That is why "
"‘danger’ is a term for sensual pleasures."

msgctxt "an6.23:2.3"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, dukkhanti … pe …"
msgstr "And why are ‘suffering’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.4"
msgid "rogoti …"
msgstr "‘disease’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.5"
msgid "gaṇḍoti …"
msgstr "‘boil’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.6"
msgid "saṅgoti …"
msgstr "‘tie’,"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.7"
msgid "paṅkoti kāmānametaṃ adhivacanaṃ?"
msgstr "and ‘bog’ terms for sensual pleasures?"

msgctxt "an6.23:2.8"
msgid ""
"Kāmarāgarattāyaṃ, bhikkhave, chandarāgavinibaddho diṭṭhadhammikāpi paṅkā na "
"parimuccati, samparāyikāpi paṅkā na parimuccati, tasmā ‘paṅko’ti kāmānametaṃ "
"adhivacananti."
msgstr ""
"Someone who is caught up in sensual greed and shackled by lustful desire is "
"not freed from suffering, disease, boils, ties, or bogs in the present life "
"or in lives to come. That is why these are terms for sensual pleasures."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.1"
msgid "Bhayaṃ dukkhaṃ rogo gaṇḍo,"
msgstr "Danger, suffering, disease, boils,"

# here I follow the Comm. But I suspect that ubhaya refers to “on both sides” (i.e. here and beyond).
#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.2"
msgid "saṅgo paṅko ca ubhayaṃ;"
msgstr "and ties and bogs both."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.3"
msgid "Ete kāmā pavuccanti,"
msgstr "These describe the sensual pleasures"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:3.4"
msgid "yattha satto puthujjano."
msgstr "to which ordinary people are attached."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.1"
msgid "Upādāne bhayaṃ disvā,"
msgstr "Seeing the danger in grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.2"
msgid "jātimaraṇasambhave;"
msgstr "the origin of birth and death,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.3"
msgid "Anupādā vimuccanti,"
msgstr "they’re freed by not grasping,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:4.4"
msgid "jātimaraṇasaṅkhaye."
msgstr "with the ending of birth and death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.23:5.1"
msgid "Te khemappattā sukhino,"
msgstr "Happy, they’ve come to a safe place,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:5.2"
msgid "diṭṭhadhammābhinibbutā;"
msgstr "extinguished in this very life."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Sabbaverabhayātītā → sabbe verabhayātītā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an6.23:5.3"
msgid "Sabbaverabhayātītā,"
msgstr "They’ve gone beyond all threats and dangers,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.23:5.4"
msgid "sabbadukkhaṃ upaccagun”ti."
msgstr "and risen above all suffering.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.23:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
